# Shadcn UI Usage Guide

## ABSOLUTE REQUIREMENT: ONLY shadcn/ui COMPONENTS ALLOWED

**CRITICAL: This project must use ONLY shadcn/ui components for ALL UI elements. ABSOLUTELY NO custom UI components should be created in this project under any circumstances.**

## UI Component Restrictions

- ✅ **ALLOWED**: All UI must come from the official shadcn/ui library
- ✅ **ALLOWED**: This project is in dark mode so make sure there are no dark colored text on dark backgrounds (and vice versa)
- ❌ **FORBIDDEN**: Creating custom UI components, styled components, or any UI elements outside of shadcn/ui
- ❌ **FORBIDDEN**: Using any other UI libraries or frameworks
- ❌ **FORBIDDEN**: Building custom buttons, forms, dialogs, or other UI primitives

## Clerk Authentication UI Requirements

**All Clerk authentication UI must follow these exact requirements:**

### Sign In/Sign Up Buttons

- **MUST** use shadcn/ui `Button` components exclusively
- **MUST NOT** use Clerk's default `<SignInButton>` or `<SignUpButton>` components
- Create custom buttons using shadcn/ui `Button` that trigger Clerk authentication modals

### Authentication Modals

- **MUST** use Clerk's modal-based authentication (`<SignIn />` and `<SignUp />` components)
- **MUST NOT** use Clerk's embedded forms or redirect-based authentication
- Authentication flows should launch in modals, not redirect to separate pages

### Implementation Pattern

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT - Custom shadcn/ui button triggering Clerk modal
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";
import { SignIn } from "@clerk/nextjs";

<Button onClick={() => setShowSignInModal(true)}>
  Sign In
</Button>

// Modal implementation using shadcn/ui Dialog
<Dialog open={showSignInModal} onOpenChange={setShowSignInModal}>
  <DialogContent>
    <SignIn />
  </DialogContent>
</Dialog>
```

## Setup Instructions

- **Initialization**: If `shadcn/ui` is not initialized, use the following command:

  ```bash
  npx shadcn@latest init
  ```

- **Component Installation**: To install a specific component (e.g., a button), use the following command:
  ```bash
  npx shadcn@latest add <component-name>
  ```
  For example, to install the button component:
  ```bash
  npx shadcn@latest add button
  ```

## Violation Examples

**❌ NEVER DO THIS:**

- Creating custom styled buttons or UI components
- Using `<SignInButton>` or `<SignUpButton>` from Clerk
- Building custom authentication forms
- Using any UI library other than shadcn/ui

**✅ ALWAYS DO THIS:**

- Use only shadcn/ui components for all UI elements
- Create authentication buttons using shadcn/ui `Button`
- Use Clerk modals (`<SignIn />`, `<SignUp />`) for authentication flows
